Plants make their own food in a process called photosynthesis, which is like cooking inside their leaves. 🌱 They take sunlight from the sun, water from the ground through their roots, and air from around them, and mix it all together to make sugar, which is their food. The Boy and the Moon   Sami was a boy who loved the moon. Every night, he sat on his roof and talked to it. One night he said, “I wish I could hold you.” The moon replied, “Okay, but bring me back before sunrise.”  The moon came down, glowing in Sami’s hands. He walked through the fields, lighting the way for fireflies and helping travelers see in the dark.  When the sun started to rise, Sami put the moon back in the sky. From that day on, the moon always shone brighter for Sami, like it was smiling at its friend
